HEADWORD: Assuetude
<hw>As"sue*tude</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>assuetudo</ets>, fr. <ets>assuetus</ets> accustomed.]</ety>
<def>Accustomedness; habit; habitual use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Assuetude</qex> of things hurtful doth make them lose their
force to hurt.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assumable</ent>⟦br⟧
